<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nikolos Rovani</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-06 23:49:07</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>For those of you having trouble with the Lucan fight, I am <BR>
pleased to announce there is a very simple way to kill him.<BR>
<BR>
I have seen groups of 30 or more train him to the east commons<BR>
zone border, out in West Freeport newbie area, and fail to<BR>
take him down. I have seen groups of 30 or more litter the<BR>
newbie area with atleast half or more of their large party<BR>
dead.<BR>
<BR>
Well, the other night, a Lucan mission was aranged on my<BR>
behalf. We threw the mission together within 15 minutes, <BR>
and were impatient, so we decided to make a go of it with<BR>
only 13 people. We killed Lucan, and I now carry Soulfire.<BR>
<BR>
This is how we did it.<BR>
<BR>
We had 1 puller. She was a level 41 Barbarian Shaman. In her <BR>
group were 3 other people. All 3 in the low teen range of levels.<BR>
<BR>
Our puller went into Lucans room in the guard house. The 3<BR>
lower level members of her group were stationed, 1 at each<BR>
door in the guard house leading out.<BR>
<BR>
Meenwhile, we had 1 detainer stationed at the north freeport zone.<BR>
The zone to noth freeport that is by the gallows poles. (the<BR>
hangmans nooses hanging in the courtyard by the broken wall).<BR>
<BR>
Meenwhile, the remaining 8 people (Myself and 7 others all of<BR>
us level 40 and above, 2 were level 50) we stayed way off to <BR>
the side in that courtyard so as to be out of agro range of<BR>
any guard pulled through there.<BR>
<BR>
While our puller stood in the guard house next to lucan, and<BR>
the 3 doormen stood at each of their doors, and our detainer<BR>
waited by the north freeport zone, our 8 member (2 groups<BR>
of 4 people each) meticulously trained and killed 1 guard at<BR>
a time to clear away all inner city guards. Ignoring any guard<BR>
inside the militia house. We also made sure to kill the guard<BR>
that is stationed by the N. FP zone.<BR>
<BR>
Once all the guards were cleared, we did a should for our<BR>
puller to start her run. When she announced the run was on,<BR>
all 3 doormen opend the doors of the militia house, allowing<BR>
her a clean run out of the building, without her having to <BR>
stop and open any doors for herself. This allowed her to exit<BR>
the guard house without taking unnecessary hits in the process<BR>
of pulling.<BR>
<BR>
She trained lucan and the 2 guards that stay by him in his room<BR>
along with 2 hall gurds all the way to that far north FP zone.<BR>
Once there, our detainer targeted Lucan, and began hailing him<BR>
over and over. Eventually, the other guards returned to the<BR>
guard house leaving lucan there alone.<BR>
<BR>
Just as we were about to advance on Lucan, 2 of the guard house<BR>
guards returned to lucans side. This was because someone in<BR>
freeport wanted to role play being a militia supporter and<BR>
trained them back to stop us from killing Lucan. This was a<BR>
bit upsetting, and quite rude on their part, but the joke was<BR>
on them, as they had to zon, and once they did, the 2 guards <BR>
again returned to their posts.<BR>
<BR>
Once the guards made their way back to the guard house a second<BR>
time, we began to move on Lucan again. By this time though, the<BR>
guard by the zone respawned.<BR>
<BR>
This was a minor inconvienience. One of the 8 people in the<BR>
combat group was a druid, so he snared the zone guard, and took<BR>
him on a tour of the city, taking a beating the whole time, but<BR>
he gave us the oppertunity we needed. This left only 7 of us<BR>
to kill Lucan. <BR>
<BR>
Well, we figured it was "no guts, no glory" time, so we attacked.<BR>
The detainer 9who was only level 30 or so) joined in with us<BR>
and we fought hard. It took a while, but Lucan finally fell. And<BR>
suprisingly, Lucan made no attempt to run away. After Lucan<BR>
fell, his skelleton immediately spawned. We turned and started<BR>
pounding on Lucans Undead form. The skelleton went down quite<BR>
a bit easier than Lucan's living form. But sadly, in the process, <BR>
our level 30 detainer who bravely joined in did not survive.<BR>
<BR>
But, I am pleased to announce, this fact did not bother him in the<BR>
least, and he actually enjoyed the experience. And I am even<BR>
happier to announce, that out of our rag-tag combat group of<BR>
only 8 people, he was the only fatality.<BR>
<BR>
I looted the Skelleton, and recovered Lucans testimony. And once<BR>
I got it, all 12 of us immediately zoned.<BR>
<BR>
Ahhhhhhhh But there was 13 members in this mission you say?<BR>
<BR>
Yes, our fearless druid who went on a sightseeing tour of<BR>
the city and newbie are with many guards hot on his heals...<BR>
<BR>
Well, I am pleased to announce, that he managed to keep ahead<BR>
of the guards, and he made his way to the other north FP zone<BR>
and came through with 2 bubbles of health left!  :-)<BR>
<BR>
So, out of 13 people to do the Lucan portion of the Soulfire<BR>
quest, 12 survived, and the mission was a success on the first<BR>
attempt.<BR>
<BR>
A couple nights after, we decided the "spur of the moment" idea<BR>
seemed to work well for us, so we did another spur of the <BR>
moment set up to raid Mistmoor to attempt to recover the hilt<BR>
from Xicotl in the castle.<BR>
<BR>
We had 2 groups (neither full) approximately the same number<BR>
of people, and we barged our way into the castle. We lucked<BR>
out and no one was camping the spawn, and we got even luckier<BR>
when Xicotl spawned a meer 15 minutes after we arrived in the<BR>
room. <BR>
<BR>
Needless to say, I looted the hilt, and we suffered no deaths<BR>
in that raid. As a matter of fact, a couple lower level Pali's<BR>
who came with us, managed to walk out with a nice little<BR>
ammount of coin, and a couple pieces of mistmoor granite which<BR>
they needed for some of their ro-armor quests.<BR>
<BR>
I want to personally thank the guilds that form multi guild<BR>
alliance "The Circle Of Karana" on the Karana server. The<BR>
guild I belong to ( "Wyrmlore Council" ) is just one of the<BR>
guilds in this alliance. But all the guilds share the same<BR>
morals and ideals, and without them, I would not be carrying<BR>
Soulfire today. I owe each and every one of them more than I<BR>
can ever hope to repay. And they all have my endless thanks<BR>
and gratituide. This is a large collection of incredibly<BR>
friendly and supportive people, and there is not a single one<BR>
of them that will ever hear the word "no" from me when they<BR>
are in need of anything.<BR>
<BR>
If any of you reading the message boar here are on the Karana<BR>
server, or are thinking of starting up a character on a server<BR>
other than the one you are on, take my advice. Make a character<BR>
on Karana, and seek out "The Circle Of Karana". If you are of<BR>
a like hearted soul, you couldn't possibly do anything more<BR>
intelligent than to seek membership within one of these<BR>
guilds. If you are fortunate enough to become a member of a<BR>
circle guild, you will find a home, filled with people who<BR>
will stand by you every step of the way in everything you<BR>
do.<BR>
<BR>
Nikolos Rovani<BR>
Paladin Of Mithaniel Marr<BR>
Devoted to "The Circle"<BR>
<BR>
"May the circle be unbroken"</font></td></tr></table>
