<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nikolos Rovani</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-21 03:00:22</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I feel your pain and I know you're frustration. And quite<BR>
often, the answer is so simple that it is seemingly<BR>
impossible to discover. Yes, this can be done. I have done<BR>
it myself on a few occasions, but you have to be VERY quick<BR>
and your system has to be almost entirely lag free.<BR>
<BR>
In a perfect worl, we would all have jedi reflexes and <BR>
pentium 900's with 10,000 gigabytes of ram, and a voodoo 6<BR>
with VR glasses and Micro Thought ESP input. But, like<BR>
most of you, I am lucky to afford the overgrown calculator<BR>
I got now... so pipe dreams aside...<BR>
<BR>
Allow me to paraphrase Mr. John Lennon:<BR>
<BR>
I get by with a little help from my friends, I get high<BR>
with a little help from my friends, gonna give a begger <BR>
some Drom's with a little hel from my friends...<BR>
<BR>
You get the idea...<BR>
<BR>
Have a friend with you. Your friend can target the beggar<BR>
and continuously hail him, while you buy the chanpagne. <BR>
This will only affor you a couple extra secondsm but it may<BR>
be just enough for your needs.<BR>
<BR>
You may also want to try buying the first droms before the<BR>
beggar even shows, and have it as your cursor for a "pre-<BR>
emptive strike".<BR>
<BR>
Also, you notice you cannot stand on the side of the bar<BR>
the beggar spawns on and purchase droms from there. You have<BR>
to purchase the drinks from the front side where "Cliff and<BR>
Norm" (the regulars - sorry for the obscrure "Cheers" <BR>
reference) stand. But you may want to give this a try...<BR>
<BR>
Try standing by the corner, and get positioned in a place <BR>
where you can see the spot the beggar spawns in, and still <BR>
be able to simply turn and activate the bartender to buy <BR>
another bottle. This way, you dont have to walk to the <BR>
beggar, it's merely a "Buy, Spin, Hand, Spin, Buy" matter.<BR>
<BR>
And remember, make good use of the escape key. After you<BR>
buy one bottle, escape out of the merchant screen, spin, <BR>
and hit your "I" key to open inventory to get the bottle<BR>
you just bought.<BR>
<BR>
One last trik<BR>
<BR>
I do not remember if Droms is "No Drop". I do know it's lore<BR>
but if it is not "NO DROP" You may want to have 4 of your<BR>
friends buy a bottle. So all 5 of you have one, and all<BR>
5 of you have the bottle set as your cursor. Hand him yours,<BR>
and as long as you have it worked out with your friends<BR>
as to who will hand YOU the droms first, second, third, etc..<BR>
you should do well that way.<BR>
<BR>
But if you use THIS method, make sure that your friends <BR>
hand the droms to YOU. If they hand it to the beggar, he<BR>
will condsider it the first bottle of 5 to come from that<BR>
person. The one getting the blanket MUST HAND ALL 5.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps...<BR>
<BR>
Nikolos "I knew I shouldnt have drank the 5th Droms" Rovani<BR>
<BR>
Paladin of Marr<BR>
Knight of The Circle</font></td></tr></table>
